  "prompt": "How much does an average subway franchise make per year?",
  "response": "The average annual revenue for a Subway franchise can vary widely based on factors like location, operating costs, and local demand. However, according to industry reports and estimates:\n\n- **Average annual sales per Subway location**: Typically range between **$400,000 to $500,000**.\n- **Profit margins**: Subway franchises generally have lower profit margins compared to other fast-food chains, often around **7% to 15%** of revenue. This translates to an average annual profit of **$28,000 to $75,000** per location.\n\nKeep in mind that these figures are averages, and individual franchise performance can differ significantly. Additionally, franchisees must account for ongoing fees, such as royalties (8% of gross sales) and advertising fees (4.5% of gross sales), which can impact profitability. \n\nProspective franchisees should carefully review the **Franchise Disclosure Document (FDD)** and consult with existing franchise owners to better understand potential earnings.",
